title: The Dominican Annexation
subtitle: Babcock returns with a treaty.
tags: event
new-page: true
view-if: year = 1869 and month >= 9 and (president = "Grant" or president = "Wade") and dominican_seen != 1
max-visits: 1
on-arrival: dominican_seen = 1

= A Treaty from the Tropics

Orville Babcock, personal secretary to President [+ president +], has returned from Santo Domingo with a draft annexation treaty. The Dominican Republic, wracked by debt and political instability, is willing — even eager — to become part of the United States.

The terms are generous to the Dominicans: the United States would assume $1,500,000 of Dominican national debt, offer the Dominican Republic the right to eventual statehood, and separately lease the strategic harbor of **Samaná Bay** at $150,000 per year for 50 years. In exchange, the United States gains a Caribbean foothold, a potential new state, and a naval base that could enforce the Monroe Doctrine across the hemisphere.

The proposal has powerful enemies. Senator Charles Sumner, chairman of the Foreign Relations Committee, regards it as a scheme to drag the country into Caribbean adventurism and burden the freedmen of the South with yet another distraction. Many Radical Republicans share his skepticism. Democrats are uniformly opposed.

[? if president = "Wade" : President Wade is personally enthusiastic about the treaty, seeing expansion as consistent with Republican ambitions. But his radical base is divided — some see Caribbean annexation as imperialism dressed up in republican clothing. ?]

[? if president = "Grant" : President Grant is personally committed to the treaty and has dispatched Babcock precisely because he wanted a favorable result. His reputation is now somewhat tied to its passage. ?]

- @push_hard: Push hard for ratification — use political capital to bring wavering Republicans on board.
- @moderate_push: Support the treaty but leave the Senate to its own deliberations.
- @oppose: Come out against the treaty and side with Sumner.
- @samanabay_only: Abandon full annexation but pursue the Samaná Bay lease alone.

@push_hard
subtitle: -2 resources. Requires Senate majority.
choose-if: resources >= 2 and sen_majority >= 2
unavailable-subtitle: [? if resources < 2: Not enough resources. ?][? if sen_majority < 2: We do not control the Senate. ?]
on-arrival: {!

Q.resources -= 2;
Q.dominican_pushed_hard = 1;

// --- Step 1: Total Senate seats from current state list ---
// Each admitted state sends 2 senators.
let totalSenate = Q.states.length * 2;
Q.dominican_total_senate = totalSenate;

// Two-thirds required for treaty ratification
let requiredVotes = Math.ceil(totalSenate * (2/3));
Q.dominican_required = requiredVotes;

// --- Step 2: Republican yea votes via faction math ---
// Base support rates per faction for this treaty:
//   Conservative: 0.85 - strongly pro-expansion
//   Moderate:     0.65 - generally supportive
//   Liberal:      0.45 - skeptical of federal overreach
//   Radical:      0.25 - Sumner wing, mostly opposed
// Pushing hard adds a flat bonus to each rate.
// High dissent within a faction reduces their yea rate —
// dissentful senators vote their conscience against the party line.

let repSeats = Q.rep_senate_r || 0;

let conYea  = 0.85 + 0.10; // push hard bonus
let modYea  = 0.65 + 0.10;
let libYea  = 0.45 + 0.08;
let radYea  = 0.25 + 0.06;

let conDis = (Q.conservative_dissent || 0) / 100;
let modDis = (Q.moderate_dissent     || 0) / 100;
let libDis = (Q.liberal_dissent      || 0) / 100;
let radDis = (Q.radical_dissent      || 0) / 100;

conYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, conYea - conDis * 0.4));
modYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, modYea - modDis * 0.4));
libYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, libYea - libDis * 0.4));
radYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, radYea - radDis * 0.4));

// Faction strength is normalized 0-100, summing to ~100 across all four
let conStr = (Q.conservative_strength || 0) / 100;
let modStr = (Q.moderate_strength     || 0) / 100;
let libStr = (Q.liberal_strength      || 0) / 100;
let radStr = (Q.radical_strength      || 0) / 100;

let repYea = Math.round(repSeats * (
    conStr * conYea +
    modStr * modYea +
    libStr * libYea +
    radStr * radYea
));

// --- Step 3: Democrat, Liberal Republican, and other yea votes ---
// Democrats almost uniformly opposed; lib reps mixed; others lean no
let demSeats   = Q.dem_senate_r   || 0;
let libRepSeats = Q.lib_senate_r  || 0;
let otherSeats = Q.other_senate_r || 0;

let demYeaVotes   = Math.round(demSeats    * 0.05);
let libRepYeaVotes = Math.round(libRepSeats * 0.40);
let otherYeaVotes = Math.round(otherSeats  * 0.30);

let totalYea = repYea + demYeaVotes + libRepYeaVotes + otherYeaVotes;
Q.dominican_yea = Math.max(0, Math.min(totalSenate, totalYea));
Q.dominican_nah = totalSenate - Q.dominican_yea;
Q.dominican_passes = (Q.dominican_yea >= requiredVotes) ? 1 : 0;

!}
go-to: treaty_result

We throw the party's weight behind ratification. Patronage is offered, arm-twisting is done behind closed doors, and the President makes clear that this is a matter of personal priority.

@moderate_push
on-arrival: {!

Q.dominican_pushed_hard = 0;

let totalSenate = Q.states.length * 2;
Q.dominican_total_senate = totalSenate;
let requiredVotes = Math.ceil(totalSenate * (2/3));
Q.dominican_required = requiredVotes;

let repSeats = Q.rep_senate_r || 0;

// No push hard bonus — base rates only
let conYea = 0.85;
let modYea = 0.65;
let libYea = 0.45;
let radYea = 0.25;

let conDis = (Q.conservative_dissent || 0) / 100;
let modDis = (Q.moderate_dissent     || 0) / 100;
let libDis = (Q.liberal_dissent      || 0) / 100;
let radDis = (Q.radical_dissent      || 0) / 100;

conYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, conYea - conDis * 0.4));
modYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, modYea - modDis * 0.4));
libYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, libYea - libDis * 0.4));
radYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, radYea - radDis * 0.4));

let conStr = (Q.conservative_strength || 0) / 100;
let modStr = (Q.moderate_strength     || 0) / 100;
let libStr = (Q.liberal_strength      || 0) / 100;
let radStr = (Q.radical_strength      || 0) / 100;

let repYea = Math.round(repSeats * (
    conStr * conYea +
    modStr * modYea +
    libStr * libYea +
    radStr * radYea
));

let demSeats    = Q.dem_senate_r   || 0;
let libRepSeats = Q.lib_senate_r   || 0;
let otherSeats  = Q.other_senate_r || 0;

let demYeaVotes    = Math.round(demSeats    * 0.05);
let libRepYeaVotes = Math.round(libRepSeats * 0.40);
let otherYeaVotes  = Math.round(otherSeats  * 0.30);

let totalYea = repYea + demYeaVotes + libRepYeaVotes + otherYeaVotes;
Q.dominican_yea = Math.max(0, Math.min(totalSenate, totalYea));
Q.dominican_nah = totalSenate - Q.dominican_yea;
Q.dominican_passes = (Q.dominican_yea >= requiredVotes) ? 1 : 0;

!}
go-to: treaty_result

We endorse the treaty publicly but leave the Senate to debate on its merits.

@oppose
on-arrival: {!

Q.dominican_pushed_hard = 0;

let totalSenate = Q.states.length * 2;
Q.dominican_total_senate = totalSenate;
let requiredVotes = Math.ceil(totalSenate * (2/3));
Q.dominican_required = requiredVotes;

let repSeats = Q.rep_senate_r || 0;

// Opposing reduces yea rates across the board — the executive
// signal matters. However, if conservative and moderate factions
// are dominant AND have low dissent, they may defy us and pass it
// anyway on their own conviction. This models the historical
// reality that a strong congressional wing can act independently.

let oppositionPenalty = 0.20;

let conYea = Math.max(0, 0.85 - oppositionPenalty);
let modYea = Math.max(0, 0.65 - oppositionPenalty);
let libYea = Math.max(0, 0.45 - oppositionPenalty);
let radYea = Math.max(0, 0.25 - oppositionPenalty);

let conDis = (Q.conservative_dissent || 0) / 100;
let modDis = (Q.moderate_dissent     || 0) / 100;
let libDis = (Q.liberal_dissent      || 0) / 100;
let radDis = (Q.radical_dissent      || 0) / 100;

// Low-dissent, high-strength factions partially resist executive opposition:
// they vote their own convictions. The stronger and more cohesive the faction,
// the more it can push back against being whipped against a bill it supports.
let conResist = Math.max(0, ((Q.conservative_strength || 0) - 30) / 100) * (1 - conDis);
let modResist = Math.max(0, ((Q.moderate_strength     || 0) - 40) / 100) * (1 - modDis);

conYea = Math.min(0.85, conYea + conResist * 0.30);
modYea = Math.min(0.65, modYea + modResist * 0.20);

conYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, conYea - conDis * 0.3));
modYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, modYea - modDis * 0.3));
libYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, libYea - libDis * 0.3));
radYea = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, radYea - radDis * 0.3));

let conStr = (Q.conservative_strength || 0) / 100;
let modStr = (Q.moderate_strength     || 0) / 100;
let libStr = (Q.liberal_strength      || 0) / 100;
let radStr = (Q.radical_strength      || 0) / 100;

let repYea = Math.round(repSeats * (
    conStr * conYea +
    modStr * modYea +
    libStr * libYea +
    radStr * radYea
));

let demSeats    = Q.dem_senate_r   || 0;
let libRepSeats = Q.lib_senate_r   || 0;
let otherSeats  = Q.other_senate_r || 0;

// Democrats barely move; lib reps and others unaffected by our stance
let demYeaVotes    = Math.round(demSeats    * 0.03);
let libRepYeaVotes = Math.round(libRepSeats * 0.35);
let otherYeaVotes  = Math.round(otherSeats  * 0.25);

let totalYea = repYea + demYeaVotes + libRepYeaVotes + otherYeaVotes;
Q.dominican_yea = Math.max(0, Math.min(totalSenate, totalYea));
Q.dominican_nah = totalSenate - Q.dominican_yea;
Q.dominican_passes = (Q.dominican_yea >= requiredVotes) ? 1 : 0;

// Political effects of public opposition regardless of outcome
Q.radical_strength  += 4;
Q.radical_dissent   -= 3;
Q.moderate_dissent  += 3;
Q.liberal_strength  += 2;
Q.dem_relation      += 3;
Q.europe_relation   += 1;

!}
go-to: treaty_result

We side with Sumner and the skeptics. The Senate will now vote without executive backing — though whether the pro-annexation factions are strong and cohesive enough to carry it on their own is another matter.

@samanabay_only
subtitle: Pursue the lease, not the annexation
on-arrival: {!

let totalSenate = Q.states.length * 2;
Q.dominican_total_senate = totalSenate;

// Lease only requires simple majority, not two-thirds
let requiredVotes = Math.floor(totalSenate / 2) + 1;
Q.dominican_required = requiredVotes;

let repSeats    = Q.rep_senate_r   || 0;
let demSeats    = Q.dem_senate_r   || 0;
let libRepSeats = Q.lib_senate_r   || 0;
let otherSeats  = Q.other_senate_r || 0;

// Lease is far less controversial — higher base rates, dissent matters less
let conDis = (Q.conservative_dissent || 0) / 100;
let modDis = (Q.moderate_dissent     || 0) / 100;

let repYeaRate   = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, 0.80 - conDis * 0.15 - modDis * 0.15));
let demYeaRate   = 0.20;
let libRepYeaRate = 0.55;
let otherYeaRate = 0.45;

let totalYea =
    Math.round(repSeats    * repYeaRate)    +
    Math.round(demSeats    * demYeaRate)    +
    Math.round(libRepSeats * libRepYeaRate) +
    Math.round(otherSeats  * otherYeaRate);

Q.dominican_yea = Math.max(0, Math.min(totalSenate, totalYea));
Q.dominican_nah = totalSenate - Q.dominican_yea;
Q.dominican_passes = 0; // full annexation never comes to vote
Q.samanabay_lease = (Q.dominican_yea >= requiredVotes) ? 1 : 0;

if (Q.samanabay_lease) {
    Q.budget         += 1;
    Q.navy_strength  += 10;
    Q.europe_relation -= 1;
    Q.moderate_strength += 2;
    Q.liberal_strength  += 2;
    Q.radical_dissent   += 1;
}

!}
go-to: samana_result

We quietly signal to Dominican negotiators that full annexation faces insurmountable opposition, but that a lease arrangement for Samaná Bay may be achievable.

@treaty_result
on-display: {!
  function drawChart() {
    var chartData = [
      { id: "yea", seats: Q.dominican_yea, color: "#228B22", outline: "#228B22" },
      { id: "nay", seats: Q.dominican_nah, color: "#8B0000", outline: "#8B0000" }
    ].filter(d => d.seats > 0);

    var width = Math.min(500, document.getElementById("content").offsetWidth - 50);
    var container = d3.select("#dominicanChart");
    if (container.empty()) {
      container = d3.select("#content").append("svg").attr("id", "dominicanChart");
    }
    container.attr("width", width).attr("height", width / 2).html("");
    var parliament = d3.parliament().width(width).innerRadiusCoef(0.4);
    container.data([chartData]).call(parliament);
  }

  if (!window.d3) {
    var s = document.createElement("script");
    s.src = "https://d3js.org/d3.v7.min.js";
    s.onload = function() {
      var p = document.createElement("script");
      p.src = "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/d3-parliament@1.0.3/build/d3-parliament.min.js";
      p.onload = drawChart;
      document.head.appendChild(p);
    };
    document.head.appendChild(s);
  } else if (!window.d3.parliament) {
    var p = document.createElement("script");
    p.src = "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/d3-parliament@1.0.3/build/d3-parliament.min.js";
    p.onload = drawChart;
    document.head.appendChild(p);
  } else {
    drawChart();
  }
!}
go-to: treaty_passes if dominican_passes = 1; treaty_fails if dominican_passes = 0

= Senate Vote on Dominican Annexation

{!<svg id="dominicanChart" style="width: 500px; height: 250px;"></svg>!}

{!<table>!}
{!<tr><td>Vote</td><td>Count</td></tr>!}
{!<tr><td><div class="box" style="background-color:#228B22; outline:2px solid;"></div> Yea</td><td>!}[+ dominican_yea +]{!</td></tr>!}
{!<tr><td><div class="box" style="background-color:#8B0000; outline:2px solid;"></div> Nay</td><td>!}[+ dominican_nah +]{!</td></tr>!}
{!<tr><td colspan="2">Two-thirds required: [+ dominican_required +] of [+ dominican_total_senate +]</td></tr>!}
{!</table>!}

@treaty_passes
on-arrival: {!

Q.dominican_annexed = 1;
Q.budget         -= 2;
Q.navy_strength  += 20;
Q.samanabay_lease = 1;
Q.europe_relation -= 2;

Q.moderate_strength  += 4;
Q.liberal_strength   += 3;
Q.radical_dissent    += 6;
Q.conservative_dissent -= 2;

Q.middle_class_rep        += 3;
Q.workers_dem             += 2;
Q.freemen_rep             -= 2;
Q.immigrant_laborers_other += 1;

// Passed despite our opposition — conservative/moderate wing feels emboldened
if (!Q.dominican_pushed_hard) {
    Q.conservative_strength += 3;
    Q.moderate_dissent      += 2;
}

!}

The Senate ratifies the annexation treaty[? if dominican_pushed_hard = 0 : , passing it without — or even against — executive support, a remarkable show of Congressional independence?]. The Dominican Republic will be formally incorporated into the United States, its debt assumed by the Treasury, and Samaná Bay opened to the U.S. Navy.

Senator Sumner delivers a thundering denunciation from the floor, warning that the Republic has taken a step toward empire. Radical newspapers echo his concern. But the moderate and conservative wings of the party celebrate a triumph of Manifest Destiny.

- @dominican_statehood_note: What becomes of Dominican statehood?

@dominican_statehood_note
on-arrival: dominican_statehood_debate = 1

The treaty grants the Dominican Republic the right to apply for statehood, but does not guarantee it. That debate will come later — and it will be fierce. For now, we have the territory, the harbor, and the debt.

@treaty_fails
on-arrival: {!

Q.dominican_fails = 1;

if (Q.dominican_pushed_hard) {
    Q.moderate_dissent   += 3;
    Q.conservative_dissent += 2;
} else {
    Q.moderate_dissent += 1;
}

Q.radical_strength += 2;
Q.radical_dissent  -= 2;
Q.liberal_strength += 1;
Q.dem_relation     += 2;
Q.europe_relation  += 1;

!}

The treaty falls short of the [+ dominican_required +] votes required for ratification, with only [+ dominican_yea +] senators in favor.

[? if dominican_pushed_hard = 1 : Despite our best efforts to bring wavering Republicans into line, too many sided with Sumner's wing of the party. The expenditure of political capital stings. ?]
[? if dominican_pushed_hard = 0 : Without executive pressure, the pro-annexation senators could not organize enough votes to clear the two-thirds bar. ?]

Sumner emerges from the chamber with the look of a man who has saved the Republic from folly. The Dominican Republic will remain independent — for now.

@samana_result
on-display: {!
  function drawChart() {
    var chartData = [
      { id: "yea", seats: Q.dominican_yea, color: "#228B22", outline: "#228B22" },
      { id: "nay", seats: Q.dominican_nah, color: "#8B0000", outline: "#8B0000" }
    ].filter(d => d.seats > 0);

    var width = Math.min(500, document.getElementById("content").offsetWidth - 50);
    var container = d3.select("#samanaChart");
    if (container.empty()) {
      container = d3.select("#content").append("svg").attr("id", "samanaChart");
    }
    container.attr("width", width).attr("height", width / 2).html("");
    var parliament = d3.parliament().width(width).innerRadiusCoef(0.4);
    container.data([chartData]).call(parliament);
  }

  if (!window.d3) {
    var s = document.createElement("script");
    s.src = "https://d3js.org/d3.v7.min.js";
    s.onload = function() {
      var p = document.createElement("script");
      p.src = "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/d3-parliament@1.0.3/build/d3-parliament.min.js";
      p.onload = drawChart;
      document.head.appendChild(p);
    };
    document.head.appendChild(s);
  } else if (!window.d3.parliament) {
    var p = document.createElement("script");
    p.src = "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/d3-parliament@1.0.3/build/d3-parliament.min.js";
    p.onload = drawChart;
    document.head.appendChild(p);
  } else {
    drawChart();
  }
!}

= Senate Vote on Samaná Bay Lease

{!<svg id="samanaChart" style="width: 500px; height: 250px;"></svg>!}

{!<table>!}
{!<tr><td>Vote</td><td>Count</td></tr>!}
{!<tr><td><div class="box" style="background-color:#228B22; outline:2px solid;"></div> Yea</td><td>!}[+ dominican_yea +]{!</td></tr>!}
{!<tr><td><div class="box" style="background-color:#8B0000; outline:2px solid;"></div> Nay</td><td>!}[+ dominican_nah +]{!</td></tr>!}
{!<tr><td colspan="2">Simple majority required: [+ dominican_required +] of [+ dominican_total_senate +]</td></tr>!}
{!</table>!}

[? if samanabay_lease = 1 : The Senate approves the Samaná Bay lease by a comfortable majority. American warships will have access to one of the finest natural harbors in the Caribbean, giving the Monroe Doctrine real teeth at a fraction of the political cost of annexation. Senator Sumner is displeased but mollified. The Dominican Republic receives $150,000 per year and keeps its sovereignty. ?]

[? if samanabay_lease = 0 : Even the more modest lease proposal fails to clear a simple majority. The Dominican question is closed for now — the Republic remains independent, its harbors beyond American reach. ?]